1 Definitions

  1. Pruning: Removing a branch from a tree
  2. Paring: Pruning one of the two descending branches from a selected branch to increase its length/support

2 Tree paring algorithm

2.0.1 Setup:

  1. Select a branch length percentile and support threshold.
  2. Set a maximum number of iterations to perform and a maximum number of tips to remove in total. Also set a max number of tips to remove during any singly PRUNE.
  3. Provide branches to be exempt from PRUNING.

2.0.2 Algorithm:

  1. Identify branches with length below the selected quantile of all branches AND below the selected support level.
  2. Of the two branches descending from this branch, select one to remove. Selection criteria could be:
    • Random, possibly with some sort of bootstrapping
    • Minimize species removed
    • Maximize support retained
    • Other?
  3. Repeat until one of the stopping conditions are met:
    • No branches that fall below the selected percentile are also below the selected support level
    • The maximum number of iterations has been reached
    • The current iteration would result in more than the maximum allowed species to be removed

2.0.3 Notes:

  1. Currently, only internal branches are considered since no support is assigned to the tips. But we could calculate support on the tips as number of genes in which they are present. However, ASTRAL trees also dont have branch lengths on the tips, so it wouldnt work for them anyways.
  2. The branch length threshold is re-calculated each iteration.
  3. The new branches inherit the support level from the retained clade. It is not currently recalculated.

4 Visualization of iterations using the minimize species removed selection criterion

4.1 Trees

plist = list()
tlist = list()
# Lists for figures per iteration

for(i in 1:nrow(in_data)){
# Loop over every pruning iteration in the input data
  
  print(paste("Iteration", i-1))
  if(i==1){
    print("Branches exempt from PRUNING labeled.")
  }
  
  iter_tree = read.tree(text=in_data[i,]$tree)
  # Read the tree into R

  tree_to_df_list = treeToDF(iter_tree)
  iter_tree_info = tree_to_df_list[["info"]]
  # Parse the tree to a data frame
  
  iter_tree_info = iter_tree_info %>% 
                    filter(node.type == "internal") %>% 
                    tidyr::separate(label, c("label","supp"), sep="_") %>%
                    bind_rows(filter(iter_tree_info, !node.type == "internal")) %>%
                    arrange(node)
  # Separates the node label from the support of the internal nodes
  
  #stop()
  
  bl_quant_10 = quantile(iter_tree_info$branch.length, 0.10, na.rm=T)
  gcf_thresh = 50
  scf_thresh = 40
  # Set the thresholds for pruning that were used
  
  iter_tree_info$supp = as.numeric(iter_tree_info$supp)
  # Convert the internal labels to numeric as the support values
  
  bl_gcf_p = ggplot(iter_tree_info, aes(x=branch.length, y=supp)) +
    geom_point(size=3, alpha=0.5) +
    geom_vline(xintercept=bl_quant_10, linetype="dashed", color=corecol(numcol=1, offset=6), size=1) +
    geom_hline(yintercept=gcf_thresh, linetype="dashed", color=corecol(numcol=1, offset=6), size=1) +
    xlab("Branch length") + 
    ylab("gCF") + 
    ggtitle(paste("Iteration", i-1)) +
    bartheme()
    if(tree_type=="concat"){
      bl_gcf_p = bl_gcf_p + scale_x_continuous(limits=c(0,0.035))
    }
  # Generate the plot of branch length vs. support
  
  bl_gcf_p = ggExtra::ggMarginal(bl_gcf_p, type="histogram", bins=50, fill=corecol(pal="wilke", numcol=1, offset=4), color="#666666")
  # Add the distributions to the plot
  
  plist[[i]] = bl_gcf_p
  # Save the plot to the list
  
  ##########
  
  iter_tree_info$low.b = ifelse(iter_tree_info$branch.length < bl_quant_10 & iter_tree_info$supp < gcf_thresh, "Y", "N")
  # Categorize each branch as being pruned or not
  
  if(tree_type == "astral"){
    xmax = 31
  }else if(tree_type == "concat"){
    xmax = 0.125
    iter_tree_info$low.b[iter_tree_info$node.type=='tip'] = "N"
  }
  # Set the max value for the x-axis in the tree figure based on the tree type
  
  b_tree = ggtree(iter_tree, size=0.8, ladderize=F, aes(color=iter_tree_info$low.b)) +
    scale_color_discrete(name = "Pare?") +
    xlim(0, xmax) +
    geom_tiplab(color="#333333", fontface='italic', size=2) +
    ggtitle(paste("Iteration", i-1)) +
    #geom_label(aes(x=branch, label=as.character(node), label.size=NA, fill="white")) +
    theme(legend.position=c(0.075,0.95))
  
  if(i==1){
    iter_tree_info$exempt = ifelse(iter_tree_info$label %in% exempt_branches$branch, "Y", "N")
    b_tree = b_tree + geom_text(aes(x=branch, label=ifelse(iter_tree_info$label %in% exempt_branches$branch, as.character(iter_tree_info$label), "")), size=2, vjust=-0.3, show.legend=F)
  }
  # Add the exempt branches as labels for the first iteration
  
  print(b_tree)
  #tlist[[i]] = b_tree
  # Generate and print the tree figure for the current iteration
}
